  "description": "In the Linux kernel through 6.3.1, a use-after-free in Netfilter nf_tables when processing batch requests can be abused to perform arbitrary read and write operations on kernel memory. This could result in a local user (with CAP_NET_ADMIN capability) crashing the system or a potential escalation of privledges.",
